constraint_artefact_type.comment: This type of fact table is used to show the activity of a job that has a well-defined beginning and end, e.g., the jobing of an order.
The type 0 dimension attributes never change and are assigned to attributes that have durable values or are described as 'Original'.
The type 1 dimension method overwrites old with new data, and therefore does not track historical data.
The type 2 dimension method tracks historical data by creating multiple records for a given natural key in the dimensional tables with separate surrogate keys and/or different version numbers.
In a fixed-width text file, data is contained in columns that are of a fixed width (meaning that each column contains a certain number of character positions).
Hubs contain a list of unique business keys with low propensity to change. Hubs also contain a surrogate key for each Hub item and metadata describing the origin of the business key.
JSON is an open standard file format and data interchange format that uses human-readable text to store and transmit data objects consisting of attribute–value pairs and arrays.
Associations or transactions between business keys (relating for instance the hubs for customer and product with each other through the purchase transaction) are modeled using link tables.
The hubs and links form the structure of the model, but have no temporal attributes and hold no descriptive attributes. These are stored in separate tables called satellites.
The periodic snapshot, as the name implies, takes a "picture of the moment", where the moment could be any defined period of time, e.g. a performance summary of a salesman over the previous month.

A transactional table is the most basic and fundamental. The grain associated with a transactional fact table is usually specified as "one row per line in a transaction", e.g., every line on a receipt.
Extensible Markup Language is a markup language that defines a set of rules for encoding documents in a format that is both human-readable and machine-readable.

data_quality_rule.name: rental_return_date_greater_than_rental_date
data_quality_rule.rule: SELECT COUNT(*) AS row_count , COUNT(DISTINCT(return_date)) AS unique_count , SUM(CASE WHEN return_date >= rental_date THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS match_count FROM rental
data_quality_rule.description: Check to ensure the return date is after or on the rental date

data_quality_rule.name: valid_customer_email_address
data_quality_rule.rule: SELECT COUNT(*) AS row_count , COUNT(DISTINCT(email)) AS unique_count , SUM(CASE WHEN email ~ '^[A-Za-z0-9._%-]+@[A-Za-z0-9.-]+[.][A-Za-z]+$' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS match_count FROM customer
data_quality_rule.description: Check to ensure the customers email address is valid

data_quality_rule.name: valid_staff_email_address
data_quality_rule.rule: SELECT COUNT(*) AS row_count , COUNT(DISTINCT(email)) AS unique_count , SUM(CASE WHEN email ~ '^[A-Za-z0-9._%-]+@[A-Za-z0-9.-]+[.][A-Za-z]+$' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS match_count FROM staff
data_quality_rule.description: Check to ensure the staff members email address is valid

glossary_entry.name: First Name
glossary_entry.definition: A given name is the part of a personal name that           identifies a person and differentiates that person           from the other members of a group who have a common surname.

glossary_entry.name: Full Name
glossary_entry.definition: A personal name or full name is the set of names by           which an individual is known and that can be recited           as a word-group, with the understanding that, taken           together, they all relate to that one individual.

glossary_entry.name: Last Name
glossary_entry.definition: A surname, family name, or last name is the portion           of a personal name that indicates a person's family.

glossary_entry.name: Password
glossary_entry.definition:
- Use both upper-case and lower-case letters (case sensitivity)
- Include one or more numerical digits
- Include special characters, such as @, #, $
- Avoid words found in a password blacklist
- Avoid words found in the user's personal information
- Avoid use of company name or an abbreviation
- Avoid passwords that match the format of calendar dates, license plate numbers, telephone numbers, or other common numbers

glossary_entry.name: Password
glossary_entry.definition: A secret word or phrase that must be used to gain           admission to a place.

glossary_entry.name: Username
glossary_entry.definition: An identification used by a person with access to a           computer, network, or online service.
